	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />What should be done for NSFs that doesn't return from the play routine?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Dwedit</b> [ Sat Mar 10, 2012 11:20 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Any specific examples?
<br />I'd try one of two things:
<br />Just make it not return, emulating it at the usual NES timing.  If it takes 5 frames to return, then treat it as if it ran for 5 frames.
<br />
<br />Or
<br />
<br />Force another interrupt anyway.  If the stack blows, oh well.  If will just wrap.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
